ned its second office in atlanta to accommodate its growing presence in northern atlanta communities and in  hb expanded again with the addition of its northcreek office values we are objective our clients’ interests guide everything we do  we are of high integrity and are passionate about our firm and profession  we strive for excellence  nothing short of this is acceptable  diligence is key in our complex and evolving profession  we rely upon teamwork we work together to accomplish a shared mission for our clients our firm and one another  we build relationships on a foundation of trust  trust is built by living these values clients homrich berg serves more than  diverse family relationships nationwide in  states managing over  billion in assets our client base is primarily made up of corporate executives entrepreneurs families family trusts and foundations and notforprofit institutions  our client retention rate is   our clients come to us at various stages in their life – marriage divorce inheritance retirement sale of a business becoming a partner having children losing a spouse deciding not to “do it themselves” anymore you name it – we have a wide range of client relationships and have experience dealing with the unique situations each new client brings to hb team to best serve each relationship homrich berg pulls from the strengths of each of its more than  employees each client service team typically includes three to four team members a principal a director or senior associate an associate and a client care coordinator tied to our commitment to providing both planning and investments expertise most of our client service professionals are either certified financial planner certificants andor chartered financial analyst charterholders and we also have a number of certified public accountants cpas on our team  all of the members of the team have experience serving families and bring a wealth of expertise from handling a wide variety of situations custodians homrich berg uses independent thirdparty custodians to hold client assets this allows clients to always have another source for verifying their assets outside of hb reports our primary custodian relationships are with charles schwab and fidelity we routinely work with new clients to transfer assets seamlessly from other custodians or advisors and handle all of the paperwork to ensure a smooth transition   interesting in learning more click here to contact us how to select an advisorlearn how to select the right financial advisor for yousee key questions you should askour geographical reach view image from our home base in atlanta we serve clients across the countrypress releasesandy berg named one of atlanta’s most admired ceos by atlanta business chroniclejuly  homrich berg named to  financial times  top registered investment advisersjune  ceo andy berg named  top advisor by barron’s magazinemarch  homrich berg appoints new principalsjanuary  homrich berg ranked as top retail ria of  by wealth managementnovember   microsoft personalized ad preferences to opt out of personalized ads in this browser your browser history must allow firstparty and thirdparty cookies and you must have your browsing experience set to not delete browsing history on exit instructions for enabling cookies and configuring your browsing history may be available in your browsers settings privacy or help documentation sign in hold on… we’re sorry but this didn’t work you can’t turn off personalized ads right now because your browser is currently blocking thirdparty cookies we can help you fix this issue let’s get started depending on what browser you use open options or settings make sure that thirdparty cookies are not blocked anymore to find out how search your browser’s help revisit httpchoicemicrosoftcomoptout and then on the “personalized ads in this browser” tile click off ext about our ads to create a more customized online experience some of the ads you may receive on microsoft websites